text:
Grand Concourse (left), west side, south from East 16lst to East 158th Street,showing the Bronx County Court House. On the right is the East 161st street side of the court house, extending west to Walton Ave. Also shown is the north end of Franz Sigel Park at East 158th Street.
1933.
Wurtr Brothers.
title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 158th Street (East)

text:
Grand Concourse, west side, from East 161st to E. 158th Streets, showing the new Bronx County Court House, which replaced the old one at Third and Brook Avenues. Views 1 and 2 are south from E. 162nd Street; view 3 is north from E. 157th Street.

Views 1,2: July 7, 1936
View 3: June 9, 1940

P. L. Sperr
